
[1]hereditary

   HERED'ITARY, a.

   1. That has descended from an ancestor. He is in possession of a large
   hereditary estate.

   2. That may descend from an ancestor to an heir; descendible to an heir
   at law. The crown of Great Britain is hereditary.

   3. That is or may be transmitted from a parent to a child; as
   hereditary pride; hereditary bravery; hereditary disease.
